olive oil
1 cucumber
2 clove garlic
½ carrot
1 packet pork mince
½ packet hoisin sauce
2 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Crispy Shallots

• Thinly slice cucumber into sticks. Finely chop garlic. Grate carrot (see ingredients).

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add hoisin sauce (see ingredients), the vinegar, soy sauce and sesame oil, and cook, stirring, until the sauce is slightly reduced, 1 minute. Remove from heat. Season with pepper.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Fill each tortilla with slaw, cucumber and hoisin pork.
• Sprinkle over crispy shallots to serve. Enjoy!